#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.p:879-5
msgid ""
"This guide is primarily designed for color screens. If you are using it for "
"the first time, we highly recommend reading this on a computer, tablet or "
"mobile. Because seeing user interface elements highlighted in color will "
"make your life easier while learning how to use KOReader. Of course you can "
"read this on your e-ink device too, but the experience will not be optimal."
msgstr ""
"Ta priročnik je prvenstveno zasnovan za barvne zaslone. Če ga uporabljaš "
"prvič, toplo priporočamo branje na računalniku, tablici ali mobilniku. "
"Barvno poudarjeni elementi uporabniškega vmesnika ti bodo namreč olajšali "
"učenje uporabe KOReaderja. Seveda ga lahko bereš tudi na svoji e-črnila "
"napravi, vendar izkušnja ne bo optimalna."

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.p:881-5
msgid ""
"You can use the search function of your browser to find a specific topic or "
"keyword (generally <b>Ctrl + F</b>). If you have a suggestion or question "
"related to this user guide, you can write to this <a href=\"https://"
"github.com/koreader/koreader/issues/11147\">GitHub discussion thread</a>."
msgstr ""
"Za iskanje določene teme ali ključne besede lahko uporabiš funkcijo iskanja "
"v brskalniku (običajno <b>Ctrl + F</b>). Če imaš predlog ali vprašanje v "
"zvezi s tem priročnikom, lahko pišeš v to <a href=\"https://github.com/"
"koreader/koreader/issues/11147\">razpravo na GitHubu</a>."

#: user_guide/en.html%2Bhtml.body.div.p:882-5
msgid ""
"Parts of the text in this guide are color coded according to their "
"categories:"
msgstr ""
"Deli besedila v tem priročniku so barvno označeni glede na njihove "
"kategorije:"

